The paper discusses privacy protection in the context of artificial intelligence and data abundance, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes an information-theoretic privacy framework using entropy, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the use of Fisher information, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the need for systematic methods for setting privacy parameters, which is a topic in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the trade-off between privacy and utility, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
